```lean
instance (k A B : Type*) [Field k] [CommRing A] [Ring B]
    [Algebra k A] [Algebra k B]
    [Algebra.IsCentral k B] :
    Algebra.IsCentral A (A ⊗[k] B) := by
  -- We need to show that A is central in the tensor product A ⊗[k] B.
  -- Given that B is central over k, we can use this property to demonstrate that A commutes with B in the tensor product.
  exact ⟨fun a => by
    -- For any a : A, we need to show that a commutes with every element in A ⊗[k] B.
    -- Specifically, we need to show that a ⊗ 1 commutes with 1 ⊗ b for any b : B.
    -- Since B is central over k, we know that for any b : B and any scalar λ : k, λ • b = b • λ.
    -- This property will help us establish the commutativity in the tensor product.
    simpa [mul_comm, mul_assoc, mul_left_comm] using
      (TensorProduct.commute_id _ _).symm⟩
```
